OL,6,F"Over the course of the inquiry the
OL,7,Ftruth will out. Wrongs will be
OL,8,Frighted. We will make sure of that.
OL,9,FWhatever it takes, however we have to
OL,10,Fdo it, and for as long as we must.
OL,11,FUnlike many, we have nothing to fear,
OL,12,Fnothing to hide or embellish. We call
OL,13,Ffor all involved across all agencies
OL,14,Fwho are called forward to finally do
OL,15,Fthe right thing. Tell the truth, admit
OL,16,Ffault if they must, accept any
OL,17,Fprofessional address should there be
OL,18,Fany, and allow this to be the moment
OL,19,Fthat makes proper change for this
OL,20,Fcountry."
